It&#39;s somewhat hard to know exactly what you mean, but I&#39;m guessing you&#39;re referring to wanting 3 different columns each going down the page.
For this I would use a parent container with flex display, and similarly, three divs for the children of the parent container which all have flex display, but instead of having row-direction, they have column (so they go down). Be sure that the parent div(s) have enough height and width to contain them :)
If you want them to &quot;start right after another&quot; then you may want to change the margin :)

    .parentContainer{
